      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CENTENARIO (2) settled worse than midfield then really worked through the gears and won pulling away last start over 1900m at Canterbury. Untested beyond 2100m but he is genuine and in the right hands. LUNAR LOVER (5) won two back at Kembla then tried very hard but missed by a neck in a similar race to this at Warwick Farm three weeks ago. Honest stayer who still gets in well at the weights and looks sure to figure again. SUBARCTIC (7) made late ground to finish just 0.7 lengths behind LUNAR LOVER when they clashed at the Farm recently. Back in form and is a big chance if he produces a similar effort this afternoon. STYLEBENDER (3) dominated over 2140m at Warwick Farm last Wednesday. Has won at this trip and while up in grade today he drops 1kg with the claim. Must be included. OAKFIELD HAWK (6) was poor last start but is back at the races with Tommy Berry aboard so he might be worth another chance.",
